Usage:
  looper daemon [flags]

Subcommands:
  install  Install the managed daemon binary
  status   Show daemon status
  start    Start the daemon
  stop     Stop the daemon
  restart  Restart the daemon
  logs     Show daemon logs

Flags:
  --force                     Overwrite existing installed daemon binary
  --full                      Show all retained daemon log lines, including rotated log files
  --lines <count>             Line count

Global Flags:
  --config <path>             Config path
  --daemon-mode <mode>        Daemon mode
  --db-path <path>            Database path
  --fix-all-pull-requests <bool> Allow fixer to inspect and fix PRs created by any author
  --gh-path <path>            GitHub CLI path
  --git-path <path>           Git binary path
  --host <host>               Server host
  --json                      Emit JSON output
  --log-dir <path>            Daemon log directory
  --looper-path <path>        Looper CLI path
  --no-custom-instructions    Disable custom instructions for debugging
  --osascript-path <path>     osascript binary path
  --port <port>               Server port
  --reviewer-loop-enabled <bool> Enable reviewer follow-up loops by default
  --reviewer-max-iterations-per-head <count> Reviewer loop max iterations per head
  --reviewer-max-iterations-per-pr <count> Reviewer loop max iterations per PR
  --reviewer-quiet-period-seconds <seconds> Reviewer loop quiet period

Examples:
$ looper daemon install
$ looper daemon start
$ looper daemon stop
$ looper daemon restart
$ looper daemon status
$ looper daemon logs --lines 50
$ looper daemon logs --full
